1. getRiskScore():-
👉 User ka final overall risk score deta hai
int risk = identity.getRiskScore();
System.out.println(risk);
✅ Output:-
65
🧠 Matlab:-
👉 Ye user ka total risk hai (roles + entitlements + policy se mila ke)

2. setRiskScore(int riskScore):-
👉 User ka risk manually set karta hai
identity.setRiskScore(80);
✅ Output (after save):-
Identity RiskScore = 80
------------------------------------------------------------------
3. getRiskScore():-
👉 Role ka khud ka risk batata hai
int roleRisk = role.getRiskScore();
System.out.println(roleRisk);
✅ Output:-
50
🧠 Matlab:-
👉 Ye role kitna dangerous hai

4. setRiskScore(int riskScore):-
👉 Role ka risk set karta hai
role.setRiskScore(70);
✅ Output:-
Role RiskScore = 70

5. getRiskScoreWeight():-
👉 Role ka contribution kitna hai final risk me
